
The whatever player chooses each time a random cell to mark, if the
cell chosen is illegal the process is repeated until a legal cell is chosen.
The naive player chooses the cells in a pattern such that for each row he chooses
all the columns in order and then moves on to the next row in order. The smart player chooses
the third column every time with an 80 percent chance, that way the winning percentage
of the smart player is guaranteed to be at least 80 percent.
By using polymorphism the same methods can be called on different player (or renderer)
types with each class providing its own behavior. This makes extending the game by adding
new players easy as there is no need to change the original code. Furthermore the code is
easily maintained since changing a specific player does not affect the rest of the code.
